content:
From the Dashboard tab, you can create, edit, or delete a dashboard using nothing but your keyboard. Use keystrokes to edit dashboards quickly and easily in Lightning Experience.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Essentials, Group (View Only), Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

Use these handy keyboard shortcuts while building or editing a dashboard:

Tab - Focus on next item in the dashboard
Shift+Tab - Focus on previous item in the dashboard
Spacebar - Select a widget to move or a widget corner to resize
Arrow keys - Move or resize a widget
Enter - Click a button
Ctrl+Z - Undo
Ctrl+Y - Redo
Ctrl+S - Save
Ctrl+N - Add widget
Esc - Cancel pending widget move or resize

As you tab through dashboard widgets, notice that the option to have a screen reader read each chartâ€™s dataset appears.
title: Edit Dashboards with Keyboard Shortcuts in Lightning Experience
